All Classes

Class Description
Bicycle
Bicycle class that extends vehicle, it has static fields for its type, gauge, cost that are used for the constructor of the vehicle
Car
Car class that extends vehicle, it has static fields for its type, gauge, cost that are used for the constructor of the vehicle
Djikstra
class for applying the Djikstra algorithm using a Priority Queue
FileReader
Main class, reads information about streets and nodes from a file, builds a graph representation of them, and then computes the minimum distance between two points, based on the vehicle driven.
GPS
Interface that provides functionalities for adding a street or a restriction in memory, and driving between two points
Map
the Map class, that stores a graph of all streets and points, and implements GPS interface for adding streets, restrictions and driving
Motorcycle
Motorcycle class that extends vehicle, it has static fields for its type, gauge, cost that are used for the constructor of the vehicle
Point
The point class, which implements Comparable interface for using the priority queue structure.
PriorityQueue<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
A generic priority queue implemented by me.
Restriction
Specific restriction that can appear on one street, like accidents or traffic jams
Street
The street class, that acts like a vertex from the start point to the end point It has a speed limit, a gauge limit and a list of roadblocks
Truck
Truck class that extends vehicle, it has static fields for its type, gauge, cost that are used for the constructor of the vehicle
Vehicle
Abstract vehicle class, extended by bicycle, motorcycle, car, truck
